<div class="content" name="Introduction" uuid="91de2312-da1f-4a45-bf24-96ca89fa7e5f"><p>This document specifies the Remote Shutdown Protocol. The
Remote Shutdown Protocol is a remote procedure call (RPC)-based protocol used
to shut down or terminate shutdown on a remote computer.</p><p>Sections 1.5, 1.8, 1.9, 2, and 3 of this specification are
normative. All other sections and examples in this specification are
informative.</p></div>